        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks WED for sending leaves and making observations on how earthworms drag them into their burrows.</p> 
<p>Doubts justice of fierce review against J. Geikie’s book [<hi rend="italic">Prehistoric Europe</hi> (1881)] in <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> [by W. B. Dawkins, 23 (1881): 309–10], but if reindeer and hippopotamus have really been found in close contact in same bed – "it tells horribly against interglacial periods".</p> 
        </abstract>
